Double agents appear when doing hard or master clue scroll emote clues. They call "I expect you to die!" upon appearing.

Contents

  • 1 Strategy
  • 2 Drops
    • 2.1 100%
    • 2.2 Tertiary
  • 3 Changes
  • 4 Trivia

Strategy[edit | edit source]

Double agents attack exclusively with melee; as such, activating Protect from Melee completely negates their damage. They are not particularly weak to any attack style.

If the double agent is killed while the player is wearing the equipment instructed to wear for the clue, Uri will immediately appear. Otherwise, the player must re-equip the items and perform the emote again.

For double agents fought in the Wilderness, only bring items you are prepared to lose.

Drops[edit | edit source]

100%[edit | edit source]

Item Quantity Rarity Price High Alch

Tertiary[edit | edit source]

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
6 July 2016
(update)

The Level 141 Double agents now appeared ingame when doing Master clue scrolls.

12 June 2014
(update)

Level 141 Double agents were added to the cache, presumably to appear when doing Elite clue scrolls, but were unused.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Their appearance is identical to Uri.
  • The phrase "I expect you to die!" is a reference to the 1964 film Goldfinger which was based on an Ian Fleming novel.

'''Double agents''' appear when doing [[Clue scroll (hard)|hard]] or [[Clue scroll (master)|master clue scroll]] emote clues. They call ''"I expect you to die!"'' upon appearing.

==Strategy==
Double agents attack exclusively with [[melee]]; as such, activating [[Protect from Melee]] completely negates their damage. They are not particularly weak to any attack style.

If the double agent is killed while the player is wearing the equipment instructed to wear for the clue, [[Uri]] will immediately appear. Otherwise, the player must re-equip the items and perform the emote again.

For double agents fought in the Wilderness, only bring items you are prepared to lose.
